[[File:Tsonag Lake, Tibet.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Tsonag Lake, from the [[Qingzang Railway]] train window]] '''Cona''', also '''Dongaii Cona''' or '''Tsonag Lake''' ({{zh|錯那湖}}, Cuonahu), is a major lake of northern [[Tibet Autonomous Region]], [[China]] and is It is located in [[Amdo County]], west of the road between [[Nagqu Town]] and [[Amdo Town]]. The lake is considered holy to the Tibetans especially in the [[Bon]] religion, as it is seen as the "soul lake" of the Razheng Living Buddha.<ref name="An刘浚2003">{{cite book|last1=An|first1=Caidan|author2=刘浚|author3=李金慧|author4=谢涛|title=Travel Guide to Tibet of China|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=n_WNBLU660AC&pg=PA18|accessdate=9 April 2012|year=2003|publisher=五洲传播出版社|isbn=978-7-5085-0374-5|page=18}}</ref> The smaller [[Ganong Lake]] lies almost adjacent to the southeast.
Its area is approximately 300 square kilometers, and it is at 4594 meters above sea level making it one of the [[List of lakes by altitude|world's higher freshwater lakes]].
Tsonag Lake can be observed on the right (west) as the train passes [[Cuonahu railway station|Tsonag Lake Railway Station]] on [[Qingzang Railway]], going south toward [[Lhasa]].<ref>[http://baike.baidu.com/view/482572.htm Tsonag Lake (Baidu Encyclopedia)] (in Chinese)</ref><ref>[http://www.hudong.com/wiki/%E9%94%99%E9%82%A3%E6%B9%96 Tsonag Lake (Hudong Encyclopedia)] (in Chinese)</ref>
==See also== * [[Qingzang Railway]] * [[Cuonahu railway station|Tsonag Lake Railway Station]]
