'''Eric Guilyardi''' is a climate scientist, professor in the department of [[meteorology]] at the [[University of Reading]]<ref>https://pagesperso.locean-ipsl.upmc.fr/ericg/</ref> and directeur de recherche [[CNRS]] at LOCEAN at [[Institute Pierre Simon Laplace]] (IPSL) in Paris, France. He is an expert of the [[El Niño]] phenomenon.<ref>http://www.climate.gov/news-features/blogs/enso/challenges-enso-today%E2%80%99s-climate-models</ref> He has been a Lead Author for the [[IPCC]] AR5 report.

